    {
      "title": "EASE Encoding Outperforms Standard List In-\ndexing EASE encoding consistently outperforms\nstandard list indexing across all instruction cate-\ngories, with the most pronounced improvements in\ncomplex instructions and list manipulations. Fig-\nure 2 breaks down EASE encoding contributions\nacross different request types. The comparison\nshows EASE improved accuracy and reduced er-\nrors across all instruction categories, while stan-\ndard list indexing produces suboptimal results due\nto index tracking challenges. This approach par-\nticularly benefits scenarios involving multiple list\noperations that would traditionally require careful\nindex arithmetic, leading to improved f1 score, se-\nmantic accuracy and patch execution.",
      "heading_level": null,
